    "body": "This patch is based upon the patch present in vim, see \r\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/commit/589edb340454e7f1b19358f129287a636d53d0e1#diff-446d78ef6820e890e59f83f0bce61d4a\r\n\r\nI'm not sure about the vim patch related to this modification (as explained in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/Merging-patches-from-upstream-Vim).\r\nThe full patch 8.2.0705 (listed on the top of the page) seems not fully relevant in adding this option.\r\n\r\nLet me know if this PR is not followings the rules of neovim, so I can edit it, or close it otherwise.\r\nFirst contribution ; read the contributing file.",
    "closed_at": "2020-05-08T16:57:23Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for the help! \r\n\r\nWe don't want to fork the Vim runtime plugins in most cases (especially syntax plugins), unless there's a very good reason. Because if Vim changes something in the same file, it takes time to figure out the differences.\r\n\r\nPlease send this change to the maintainer, listed at the top of the file.\r\n\r\nAnd also send the change to https://github.com/vim/vim, mentioning that you\r\nalready sent the change to the maintainer. Please link to it from here.",
            "created_at": "2020-05-08T16:57:15Z",
